   NEW YORK _ The four police officers accused of murder in the shooting death of Amadou Diallo plan to testify in their own defense at their trial next month and are leaning toward choosing a trial by a judge instead of a jury, according to their lawyers.
NEW YORK (AP) -- Four white police officers were charged with   murder Wednesday for killing an unarmed African immigrant in a hail  of 41 bullets -- a shooting that has led to months of protests and a  painful examination of police tactics and race relations.
